## §2. REGIME ARCHITECTURE

### Principle
All logic conditional on continuous market regime scores.

### Specification

**Regime Vector:**
$$
\mathbf{R} = \left( R_{\text{vol}}, R_{\text{trend}}, R_{\text{liq}}, R_{\text{micro}}, \frac{d\mathbf{R}}{dt}, \text{Conf} \right)
$$

| Component | Range | Description |
|-----------|-------|-------------|
| $R_{\text{vol}}$ | [0, 1] | 0=low, 1=extreme volatility |
| $R_{\text{trend}}$ | [-1, 1] | -1=down, +1=up trend |
| $R_{\text{liq}}$ | [0, 1] | 0=crisis, 1=abundant liquidity |
| $R_{\text{micro}}$ | [0, 1] | 0=toxic, 1=stable microstructure |
| $d\mathbf{R}/dt$ | ℝ | Regime velocity (transition rate) |
| Conf | [0, 1] | Classification confidence |

**Confidence:** $\text{Conf} = 1 - H(\mathbf{p})$ (normalized entropy)

### Implementation

```python
@dataclass
class RegimeVector:
    volatility: float      # [0, 1]
    trend: float           # [-1, 1]
    liquidity: float       # [0, 1]
    microstructure: float  # [0, 1]
    d_volatility: float
    d_trend: float
    d_liquidity: float
    d_microstructure: float
    confidence: float
    
    def is_transitioning(self, threshold: float = 0.1) -> bool:
        return any(abs(v) > threshold for v in 
                   [self.d_volatility, self.d_trend, self.d_liquidity, self.d_microstructure])
    
    def effective_volatility(self) -> float:
        return self.volatility + (0.1 if self.d_volatility > 0 else 0)

class AlphaBase(ABC):
    @property
    @abstractmethod
    def volatility_range(self) -> Tuple[float, float]: pass
    
    @property
    @abstractmethod
    def min_liquidity(self) -> float: pass
    
    @property
    @abstractmethod
    def min_confidence(self) -> float: pass
    
    def is_compatible(self, r: RegimeVector) -> bool:
        if r.confidence < self.min_confidence:
            return False
        v = r.effective_volatility()
        return (self.volatility_range[0] <= v <= self.volatility_range[1] and 
                r.liquidity >= self.min_liquidity)
```

