## §3. OPPORTUNITY THRESHOLD

### Principle
Trade only when tail-risk-adjusted return exceeds costs.

### Specification

**Expected Risk-Adjusted Return:**
$$
\text{ERAR} = \frac{\mathbb{E}[\text{PnL}] - \lambda \cdot \text{CVaR}_{95}}{\text{Cost}} \cdot \Omega_{\text{adj}}
$$

**Cost Model:**
$$
\text{Cost} = C_{\text{spread}} + C_{\text{slip}} \cdot \phi^{0.6} + P_{\text{adv}} \cdot \lambda_K + C_{\text{opp}}
$$

| Component | Formula |
|-----------|---------|
| $C_{\text{slip}}$ | $\sigma \sqrt{Q/\text{ADV}}$ |
| $C_{\text{opp}}$ | $\mathbb{E}[R_{\text{alt}}] \cdot t_{\text{hold}}$ |
| $\Omega_{\text{adj}}$ | $\text{clip}(1 + 0.1 \cdot \text{skew}, 0.5, 1.5)$ |

**Trade Condition:** $\text{ERAR} \geq \gamma$

### Implementation

```python
@dataclass
class ERAR:
    expected_pnl: float
    cvar_95: float
    skewness: float
    spread_bps: float
    participation: float
    adverse_prob: float
    kyle_lambda: float
    holding_days: float
    alt_return_bps: float
    tail_lambda: float = 1.0
    
    def cost(self) -> float:
        return (self.spread_bps + 
                self.kyle_lambda * (self.participation ** 0.6) * 10000 +
                self.adverse_prob * self.kyle_lambda * 10000 +
                self.alt_return_bps * self.holding_days / 252)
    
    def omega_adj(self) -> float:
        return np.clip(1 + 0.1 * self.skewness, 0.5, 1.5)
    
    def compute(self) -> float:
        cost = self.cost() / 10000
        if cost <= 0:
            return 0.0
        return ((self.expected_pnl - self.tail_lambda * abs(self.cvar_95)) / cost * self.omega_adj())
    
    def should_trade(self, gamma: float) -> bool:
        return self.compute() >= gamma
```

