## §6. TREND AVOIDANCE

### Principle
Avoid counter-trend positions against confirmed trend.

### Specification

**Trend Pressure Index:**
$$
\text{TPI} = H \cdot \text{AC}_{\text{weighted}} \cdot \text{VolConf} \cdot \text{BreadthConf}
$$

| Component | Formula |
|-----------|---------|
| $H$ | Hurst exponent (>0.5 = trending) |
| $\text{AC}_w$ | $0.5|\text{AC}(1)| + 0.3|\text{AC}(5)| + 0.2|\text{AC}(20)|$ |
| VolConf | Up-volume ratio (for uptrend) |
| BreadthConf | % stocks above MA (for uptrend) |

**Prohibition:** No counter-trend when $\text{TPI} \geq 0.3$

### Implementation

```python
@dataclass
class TrendPressure:
    hurst: float
    ac_1: float
    ac_5: float
    ac_20: float
    up_vol_ratio: float
    pct_above_ma: float
    drift: float
    
    def hurst_signal(self) -> float:
        return max(0, self.hurst - 0.5) * 2
    
    def ac_signal(self) -> float:
        return 0.5*abs(self.ac_1) + 0.3*abs(self.ac_5) + 0.2*abs(self.ac_20)
    
    def vol_conf(self) -> float:
        return self.up_vol_ratio if self.drift > 0 else 1 - self.up_vol_ratio
    
    def breadth_conf(self) -> float:
        return self.pct_above_ma if self.drift > 0 else 1 - self.pct_above_ma
    
    def compute(self) -> float:
        return self.hurst_signal() * self.ac_signal() * self.vol_conf() * self.breadth_conf()
    
    def is_strong(self, threshold: float = 0.3) -> bool:
        return self.compute() >= threshold
    
    def direction(self) -> str:
        return 'up' if self.drift > 0.001 and self.ac_1 > 0 else ('down' if self.drift < -0.001 and self.ac_1 < 0 else 'neutral')
    
    def allows_trade(self, side: str) -> bool:
        if not self.is_strong():
            return True
        d = self.direction()
        return not ((side == 'BUY' and d == 'down') or (side == 'SELL' and d == 'up'))
```

